5. Labs and clinical skills front loaded at the beginning of the week
6. Thursday/Friday free afternoons
7. Normal Exams on Fridays and a 3 day weekend after finals
8. P/F, with class rank (if student wants to know)
9. No “homework” assignments

Steps to make med school better:

1. Systems based approach in every school
2. Ppts organized by specialty - path has pathophys, morphology, and clinical findings (for example)
3. No mandatory lectures. Period.
4. Board prep provided for all students (Amboss, Osmosis, Sketchy)
As it is, you’re better off quickly reviewing slide sets, making a few flash cards, and using 3rd party resources

Medical education isn’t difficult cuz of the content, it’s difficult cuz of the disarray of curricula, teaching styles, and expectations for all students to drop their lives in lieu of a grade. 

Organize that, we have a much, much better job at teaching future physicians.
